    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Neurological manifestations of SARS-CoV-2 infection described in isolated case reports and single institutions do not accurately reflect the clinical spectrum of disease across all geographies in a global pandemic. Data collected during peak of the Covid-19 pandemic from stroke centers in five states reveal few similarities to what has recently been published. Given the diversity in phenotype, we caution policymakers and health care providers when considering cerebrovascular complications from SARS-CoV-2 infection.</jats:p>",
